            SELECT filtered.sort, l.*, d.field_number, d.value
            FROM jg_rg_lead l
            INNER JOIN jg_rg_lead_detail d ON d.lead_id = l.id
            INNER JOIN
            (
                SELECT @rownum:=@rownum + 1 as sort, id
                FROM
                (
                    SELECT distinct l.id
                    FROM jg_rg_lead l
                    INNER JOIN jg_rg_lead_detail d ON d.lead_id = l.id
                    
                    WHERE (l.form_id=1 AND l.status = 'active')
                    ORDER BY (l.id+0) DESC
                    LIMIT 0,20
                ) page
            ) filtered ON filtered.id = l.id

            ORDER BY filtered.sort

<h1>Gravity Forms MailChimp Add-On v4.2</h1>

<p>v4.0+ of the Gravity Forms MailChimp Add-On is an extremely important update and we recommend ALL users update as soon as possible.  The MailChimp Add-On has been updated to work with v3.0 of the MailChimp API.  MailChimp will be discontinuing support and functionality for v2.0 of the MailChimp API that prior versions of this Add-On utilized.</p>
<p>If you do not update to this new version of the MailChimp Add-On, your site may not be able to communicate with MailChimp.  Please update immediately.</p>

<h2>What's New in v4.2</h2>
<ul>
<li>Added additional logging when checking if a user's subscription status.</li>
<li>Added existing member object as sixth parameter of "gform_mailchimp_subscription" filter.</li>
<li>Fixed PHP warning when attempting to check for existing interests when member did not belong to any interest categories.</li>
<li>Fixed Fatal error that happened in certain situations.</li>
<li>Fixed existing interest categories not being properly associated to subscription object.</li>
<li>Fixed an issue with subscriptions not being created due to empty merge fields.</li>
<li>Fixed an issue which could prevent the feed groups being converted to interest categories when upgrading from older versions of the add-on.</li>
<li>Fixed inability to use double opt-in with existing memebers.</li>
<li>Fixed API response error handling; API key was incorrectly shown as valid when a 403 Forbidden error was returned.</li>
<li>Fixed an issue with the field value used for interest category logic evaluation.</li>
<li>Restored GFMailChimp::get_group_setting_key() for use when upgrading from older versions of MailChimp Add-On.</li>
<li>Restored double opt-in support for members who are being resubscribed to a list they are unsubscribed from.</li>
<li>Disabled double opt-in support for members who are being resubscribed to a list they are unsubscribed from. (Member will be automatically subscribed to the list. This is a temporary workaround for an issue with the MailChimp API.)</li>
<li>Re-introduced support for "gform_mailchimp_keep_existing_groups" filter.</li>
</ul>

2018-03-15 11:48:39.370630 - DEBUG --> 
            SELECT filtered.sort, l.*, d.field_number, d.value
            FROM jg_rg_lead l
            INNER JOIN jg_rg_lead_detail d ON d.lead_id = l.id
            INNER JOIN
            (
                SELECT @rownum:=@rownum + 1 as sort, id
                FROM
                (
                    SELECT distinct l.id
                    FROM jg_rg_lead l
                    INNER JOIN jg_rg_lead_detail d ON d.lead_id = l.id
                    
                    WHERE (l.form_id=2 AND l.status = 'active')
                    ORDER BY (l.id+0) DESC
                    LIMIT 0,20
                ) page
            ) filtered ON filtered.id = l.id

            ORDER BY filtered.sort

            SELECT filtered.sort, l.*, d.field_number, d.value
            FROM jg_rg_lead l
            INNER JOIN jg_rg_lead_detail d ON d.lead_id = l.id
            INNER JOIN
            (
                SELECT @rownum:=@rownum + 1 as sort, id
                FROM
                (
                    SELECT distinct l.id
                    FROM jg_rg_lead l
                    INNER JOIN jg_rg_lead_detail d ON d.lead_id = l.id
                    
                    WHERE (l.form_id=10 AND l.status = 'active')
                    ORDER BY (l.id+0) DESC
                    LIMIT 0,20
                ) page
            ) filtered ON filtered.id = l.id

                    LIMIT 0,20
                ) page
            ) filtered ON filtered.id = l.id
